Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
cutRow(25.10)                                                    cutRow(25.10)

Name
       cutRow  -  Cuts site rows within an area or that intersect with the se-
       lected object(s)

Syntax
        cutRow

       [-help]

       [-area <box >| -object <string >| -selected  |  -fromIo  {<left  bottom
       right top>}]

       [-halo  <float>|  {-leftGap <float>| -rightGap <float >| -topGap <float
       >| -bottomGap <float>}]

       [-site <name>]

       [-keepCell]

       Cuts site rows within an area or that intersect with the  selected  ob-
       ject(s).  Use  this  command after rows have been created.  Only insts,
       hinsts, place blockages, route blockages,  power  domains,  groups,  or
       bumps can participate in row splitting.

       Note: The default behavior is to cut rows that intersect with placement
       blockages and macros.

Parameters
       -area <box>
              Rows  will  be  cut  within the specified box. box is a tcl list
              containing 4 items. The items are, in order: LLX, LLY, URX, URY.

              Note: The -halo parameter cannot be applied -area used.

              Data_type: box, optional

       -bottomGap <float>
              Specifies the additional gap to be provided on the  bottom  side
              of the specified or selected object.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -fromIo {<left bottom right top>}
              Cuts  core  rows to keep them away from I/O cells in the minimum
              distance specified. Left means for IO cells on left side of  die
              box, and so forth.

              Data_type: box, optional

       -halo <float>
              Specifies  additional  space  to be provided on the top, bottom,
              left, and right sides of the objects causing  rows  to  be  cut.
              Rows  are  cut  to the expanded boundary. The same value is used
              for all sides.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each cutRow parameter. For a detailed descrip-
              tion of the command and all of its parameters, use the man  com-
              mand:

              man cutRow

       -keepCell
              Specifies that all cells that are placed inside the cut row area
              will not be unplaced.

              Default: All cells inside the cut rows will be unplaced.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -leftGap <float>
              Specifies  the additional gap to be provided on the left side of
              the specified or selected object.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -object <string>
              Specifies the name of an intersecting object. Rows  that  inter-
              sect this object are cut. Only one name may be specified.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -rightGap <float>
              Specifies the additional gap to be provided on the right side of
              the specified or selected object.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -selected
              Specifies  that  the  rows  that intersect with the selected ob-
              ject(s) will be cut.

              Note:  Only supports inst, hinst,  power  domain,  group,  place
              blockage, route_blockage, and bump as selected object(s).

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -site <name>
              Rows containing site name will be cut.

              Default: All rows in the core box are cut.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -topGap <float>
              Specifies  the  additional gap to be provided on the top side of
              the specified or selected object.

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
              * The following command cuts the rows containing sites  of  type
                SITE_FE283001 in the specified area:

                cutRow  -site  SITE_FE283001  -area  124.975  138.123  237.378
                223.38

              * The following command cuts the rows intersecting with selected
                objects, with a 0.5 micron halo:

                cutRow -selected -halo 0.5

              * The following command cuts the rows intersecting with the  ob-
                ject named fuu, with additional bottom gap of 0.5 microns:

                cutRow -object fuu -bottomGap 0.5

